<task id="AIPL-014" project="AI Platform Foundation Phase 1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement RagIndexingJobHandler — Service Bus Background Indexing</title>
    <phase>2 — Workstream A: Retrieval Foundation</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api, jobs, retrieval, indexing</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPL-013</dependencies>
    <blocks>AIPL-015 (KnowledgeBaseEndpoints)</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement RagIndexingJobHandler — a Service Bus-triggered background job handler that
    calls RagIndexingPipeline after a document analysis job completes. The handler follows
    the existing BackgroundJobHandlerBase pattern used by other job handlers in the codebase.

    Also update AnalysisOrchestrationService to emit a RagIndexingJob to the Service Bus queue
    after analysis completes, so indexing happens automatically without blocking the analysis response.

    The job must be idempotent — re-queuing for the same document should produce the same result.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer familiar with Azure Service Bus, BackgroundService patterns in .NET 8,
    and the existing Spaarke job handler framework.
  </role>

  <goal>
    RagIndexingJobHandler processes Service Bus messages and calls RagIndexingPipeline.
    AnalysisOrchestrationService emits the job after analysis. Idempotency key prevents
    duplicate indexing. Unit tests pass.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Use BackgroundService + Service Bus — no Azure Functions</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-004">Idempotent handler: IdempotencyKey = "{tenantId}:{documentId}". Emit JobOutcome on completion.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-004">Handler must be deterministic — same input always produces same output</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Indexing must complete within 60 seconds of analysis (NFR-11)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-platform-enhancements-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagIndexingPipeline.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-004-job-contract.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Job handler pattern" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/Handlers/">
        Look for existing BackgroundJobHandlerBase implementations to understand the pattern.
        RagIndexingJobHandler must follow the same structure.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read existing job handler implementations">
      Read at least one existing BackgroundJobHandlerBase implementation from Services/Jobs/Handlers/
      to understand the pattern: job message shape, idempotency key, JobOutcome emission.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Create RagIndexingJob message class">
      Create src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Jobs/RagIndexingJob.cs:
      - DocumentId: string
      - TenantId: string
      - AnalysisId: string
      - DocumentUrl: string (or SpeFileReference)
      - TriggeredAt: DateTimeOffset
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Create RagIndexingJobHandler.cs">
      Create src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/Handlers/RagIndexingJobHandler.cs:
      - Extends BackgroundJobHandlerBase&lt;RagIndexingJob&gt;
      - IdempotencyKey: $"{job.TenantId}:{job.DocumentId}"
      - HandleAsync: fetch document bytes → call RagIndexingPipeline.IndexDocumentAsync()
      - Emit JobOutcome.Succeeded/Failed with timing info
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Update AnalysisOrchestrationService to emit job">
      After analysis completes in AnalysisOrchestrationService, enqueue RagIndexingJob to
      Service Bus. Use existing Service Bus client pattern from the codebase.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Register handler in Program.cs">
      Register RagIndexingJobHandler following existing handler registration pattern.
      Update DI count in CLAUDE.md.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Write unit tests">
      Create tests/unit/Services/Jobs/Handlers/RagIndexingJobHandlerTests.cs:
      - Test: successful job calls RagIndexingPipeline with correct parameters
      - Test: idempotency key is "{tenantId}:{documentId}"
      - Test: JobOutcome.Succeeded emitted on successful indexing
      - Test: JobOutcome.Failed emitted when pipeline throws, with error info
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify build and tests">
      Run: dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/ --filter "RagIndexingJobHandler"
      Both must pass.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and test</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage changes</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/Handlers/RagIndexingJobHandler.cs</output>
